dent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The success rate of obtaining research a group-leader (or equivalent) position is not very high and requires </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">extraordinary commitment to work. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The direct reason that women are most-often the primary care</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">givers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of children and will find it impossible to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be competitive in a career system where twelve plus hour work days, demanding travel to conferences and constantly writing grants an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d papers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">at ho</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">me and on weekends are the norm</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> cannot be underestimated. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">As the reality of this career choice becomes appare</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nt t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">o women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> they often choose something else</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> either </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in order to have a child or</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman';